2026-04-16 07:51:08 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='hypothesis' action_type=None action_target=None action_description=None suspected_components=['Power supply module to control module cables (polarity/cross-connection)'] hypothesis_explanation='The green LED on the power supply module being off indicates that the 12V supply is either not connected or its polarity is reversed. The red LED on the control module (inverted cables indicator) illuminates when the 12V and 0V lines are swapped. This suggests that the cables connecting the power supply module to the control module are reversed (polarity swapped). Because of this, not only does the power supply indicator not glow, but the rest of the circuit beyond the control module will also not get proper voltage, so the lamp will not light up even if the switch is operated. The likely root cause is incorrect connection (crossed polarity) between the power supply and control module.'
